I’m thrilled to share the exciting news that this past year I worked with @aliciakeys @sheisthemusic and @everywomanstudios on a remarkable documentary entitled #Uncharted. It’s been an incredible experience and I can’t wait for the world to witness not only my journey as a songwriter, artist, producer, but also the captivating stories of the other remarkable women featured in this film. On June 10, at the @tribeca film festival, the world will watch as we unveil our narratives, embark on a transformative journey, and radiate in our personal growth!

With inspirations coming from growing up in the church and a natural ability to handle a variety of instruments, @lanitasmith is ready for her name to be recognized as a top artist, producer, and songwriter.

Now having performed around the world and on national television, Lanita is breaking barriers and bringing to light how underrated and undervalued black and brown women are in the world of music. #UnchartedTheDoc brings this same message to light, and showcases Lanita’s triple threat energy. #LetsGetHerCharted

Today, live in the moments you create. Love on yourself and others. Even in the midst of all life’s many obstacles, we still have so many things to be grateful for. Happy Thanksgiving Family
